H.E Governor Mai Mala Buni visited Nasarawa-Eggon near Lafia in Nasarawa State today to condole with the family of the immediate past National Vice Chairman (North-Central) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Alhaji Zakari Abdullahi Idde who died and was buried in the town today. Alhaji Zakari Idde died at the age of 56 years old. He is survived by his aged mother, Hadjiya Zainab and 31 children. He also left behind four widows. He was, until his death, the Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Lower Niger River Basin Development Authority. H.E Governor Buni, who was received at the residence of the deceased by the Deputy Governor of Nasarawa State Dr Emmanuel Agbadu Akabe, prayed Almighty Allah to grant the late Alhaji Zakari Idde eternal repose in al-Jannatul Firdausi. The governor also personally condoled with the mother of the deceased Hadjiya Zainab who thanked him on behalf of the family for the condolence visit. H.E Governor Buni was accompanied to Nasarawa-Eggon by the Deputy National Chairman of the APC (North) Alhaji Lawal Shuaibu, APC Yobe State Treasurer Alhaji Mohammed Gadaka and Commissioner for Information and Home Affairs Abdullahi Bego. Bego Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA